# Mobile Keyboard Avoiding

The keyboard MUST never cover interactive inputs or action buttons. This is a recurring issue on Android especially with bottom-sheet modals.

## The Correct Pattern for Bottom-Sheet Modals

**WRONG — keyboard covers buttons:**
```tsx
// behavior="padding" + ScrollView with justifyContent="flex-end" = buttons stay under keyboard
<KeyboardAvoidingView behavior="padding" style={{ flex: 1, justifyContent: "flex-end" }}>
  <View style={modalCard}>
    <ScrollView>...</ScrollView>
    <Button /> {/* ← covered by keyboard on Android */}
  </View>
</KeyboardAvoidingView>
```

**CORRECT — always use this structure:**
```tsx
<Modal>
  <KeyboardAvoidingView
    style={{ flex: 1 }}
    behavior={Platform.OS === "ios" ? "padding" : "height"}
  >
    {/* marginTop: "auto" pins the card to the bottom of available space */}
    {/* When keyboard opens, behavior="height" shrinks the container */}
    {/* The card shrinks too, making inner ScrollView scrollable */}
    <View style={[styles.modalCard, { marginTop: "auto" }]}>
      <ScrollView
        keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled"
        showsVerticalScrollIndicator={false}
        contentContainerStyle={{ paddingBottom: 24 }}
      >
        {/* All form fields AND action buttons go inside ScrollView */}
        <TextInput ... />
        <View style={{ flexDirection: "row", gap: 8 }}>
          <Button label="Cancel" />
          <Button label="Save" />
        </View>
      </ScrollView>
    </View>
  </KeyboardAvoidingView>
</Modal>
```

## Rules

- ALWAYS use `behavior={Platform.OS === "ios" ? "padding" : "height"}` — never use `behavior="padding"` on Android for modals.
- ALWAYS put `marginTop: "auto"` on the modal card (not `justifyContent: "flex-end"` on the overlay).
- ALWAYS place both inputs AND action buttons (Cancel / Save / Submit) INSIDE the `ScrollView` so they scroll into view.
- NEVER place buttons outside the ScrollView if they are below form inputs.
- For full-screen forms (not modals), wrap the entire screen in `KeyboardAvoidingView` with `behavior={Platform.OS === "ios" ? "padding" : undefined}` and use a `ScrollView` with `keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled"` and a generous `paddingBottom` (at least 100).
- Always import `Platform` from `react-native` when using platform-specific behavior.

## Full-screen form pattern

```tsx
<KeyboardAvoidingView
  style={{ flex: 1 }}
  behavior={Platform.OS === "ios" ? "padding" : undefined}
>
  <ScrollView
    keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled"
    contentContainerStyle={{ padding: 16, paddingBottom: 120 }}
  >
    <TextInput ... />
    <TouchableOpacity style={styles.submitBtn}>
      <Text>Submit</Text>
    </TouchableOpacity>
  </ScrollView>
</KeyboardAvoidingView>
```
